         It matters not what the effects are. What matters is that the level III effect items come off of raid level encounters (about 85% of them) most of the items with a desirable effect are already items typically rewarded to class that dont benefit from them the way other classes might.</P><P>An FBSS is EASY to get, and so a melee class can equip himself reasonably well with a haste effect untill he stumbles across a better one while just leveling up or raiding. It isn't the same for casters. WE MUST RAID to get effects that are worth having in the 50+ game. That is totally rediculous. spell level should not dictate what effects it can receive, straight percentages should be applied or easier to obtain items need to be added (similar to the FBSS wich has no stats or ac, only the haste)</P><P>&lt;a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=94336"&gt;<BR>&lt;img src="http://crystaloracle.darktech.org/eqgrouping/images/beur/MakaSig.jpg"&gt;&lt;/a&gt;<BR><b>The destination is never important, only the journey.</b><a href="#top"><img src="icon_go_up.gif" height="15" width="15" border="0" align="right" alt="Go to Top of Page"></a></font></td>
