         Yeah they did not do a very good job here.</P><P>First, the levels should work as suggested above, more like AA abilities.  The way it stands now only level 3 items are worth a shit to the post 60 player.  Hell even a level 2 item isnt that attractive to anyone over level 50...</P><P>Second, there was not a good thought process to distribute the best effects onto high level items.  Some high level items have crappy level 1/2 effects, and some ridiculously low level items have level 3 effects.</P><P>Finally, the items they chose for these effects, and what they chose to put on each of those items, dont make much sense.  Class specific items practically scream FOCUS EFFECT, and yet very few, if any, received them.  And yet, none of my various levels of Velious armor got an effect.  None of my Necro sky items did either.  I am not sure if any Necro only items did.</P><P>Oh well.  It is a start, hopefully they will keep at it and we will see another patch in a week or so with a lot more changes, and maybe even some intelligent changes to the way the system works.</P><P>Sayleth</P><P>And I looked, and behold a pale horse: and his name that sat on him was Death - Revelation 6:8<a href="#top"><img src="icon_go_up.gif" height="15" width="15" border="0" align="right" alt="Go to Top of Page"></a></font></td>
